~ teach_if
starfish: Let‚Äôs start with the [b]if statement[/b]. It checks a condition, which is either [b]True[/b] or [b]False[/b], and only runs the code inside if the condition is True. Think of it like a fork in the road: your program only takes the path when the condition allows it.
starfish: The basic syntax looks like this (each '->' represents one indentation level): [b][br]if condition:[br]-># code runs if condition is True[/b]
starfish: See how the line with the arrow is shifted to the right? This spacing, called [b]indentation[/b], tells Python which code belongs inside the if statement.
starfish: Would you like me to explain why indentation is so important?
