~ indentation
starfish: In Python, indentation shows which lines of code belong together. Unlike some other languages, you cannot skip it‚Äîit‚Äôs how Python understands your code.
starfish: Python uses [b]spaces or tabs[/b] at the beginning of a line to define blocks. If your spacing is wrong, Python might crash or do something completely different than what you expected.
starfish: For clarity in our examples, I‚Äôm using '->' to represent one indentation level. In real Python, you‚Äôll use actual spaces or tabs, but this makes it easier to see which code belongs where.
starfish: Always keep indentation consistent. Even one missing space or tab can break your program!
