~ teach_elif
starfish: Sometimes one condition isn‚Äôt enough. That‚Äôs where [b]elif[/b] and [b]else[/b] come in‚Äîthey let your program check multiple conditions and pick the correct path.
starfish: Python evaluates conditions from top to bottom. As soon as it finds one that‚Äôs True, it runs that block and ignores the rest. This way, only one path is ever taken.
starfish: The full structure looks like this:
starfish: if condition1:[br]-># runs if condition1 is True[br]elif condition2:[br]-># runs if condition1 is False and condition2 is True[br]else:[br]-># runs if all conditions are False. 
starfish: This makes your code predictable and easy to debug.
