~ teach_comparisons
starfish: To create conditions, we use [b]comparison operators[/b]. These compare values and always give True or False, which your program uses to decide what to do.
starfish: Some common comparison operators are: == (equal to), != (not equal to), > (greater than), < (less than), >= (greater or equal), <= (less or equal).
starfish: Here‚Äôs a real example with if, elif, and else:
starfish: score = 85[br]if score >= 90:[br]->print('Grade A')[br]elif score >= 75:[br]->print('Grade B')[br]else:[br]->print('Grade C'). 
starfish: Since the score is 85, the first condition is false, the second is true, so Python prints [b]Grade B[/b].
