~ teach_logical
starfish: Sometimes a decision depends on more than one condition. Python lets you combine them using [b]logical operators[/b], which makes your rules smarter.
starfish: The main logical operators are [b]and[/b], [b]or[/b], and [b]not[/b]. 'and' requires all conditions to be True, 'or' requires at least one to be True, and 'not' reverses True to False (or False to True).
starfish: Here‚Äôs an example with multiple conditions
starfish: temperature = 25[br]is_raining = False[br]if temperature >= 20 and temperature <= 30 and not is_raining:[br]->print('Perfect day!'). 
